WEBVTT

00:14.472 --> 00:17.392
[siren blaring in distance]

00:18.018 --> 00:19.644
[man over megaphone] Mr. Miller?

00:21.146 --> 00:23.690
Is everyone okay in there?

00:23.773 --> 00:24.858
[car door opens]

00:25.734 --> 00:27.152
Agent Ford, FBI.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.239
Here, sir.

00:31.322 --> 00:33.908
[man over megaphone]
We want to know what's going on.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.871
If you harm anyone,
it will not end well for you!

00:37.954 --> 00:39.456
Special Agent Holden Ford.

00:41.166 --> 00:42.876
-Ninkovich.
-Is he talking?

00:42.959 --> 00:44.294
Not making sense. Been briefed?

00:44.377 --> 00:46.254
On the way over.
Five people still in there?

00:46.337 --> 00:49.090
A security guard, the secretary,
three guys from the line.

00:49.174 --> 00:50.425
[door opens]

00:52.010 --> 00:54.971
-[Miller] Where is she?
-[Ninkovich] Take it easy, Mr. Miller.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.723
[Miller] I want my wife!

00:56.806 --> 00:59.476
Put the gun down,
step away from Ms. Curtwell.

00:59.559 --> 01:04.022
-[Miller] I have asked you--
-We need to see that everyone is unharmed.

01:04.606 --> 01:05.482
You gonna shoot me?

01:05.982 --> 01:09.694
If you do not abide by our terms,
and soon--

01:09.778 --> 01:11.279
You can't see me!

01:11.362 --> 01:14.574
I'm warning you,
our patience is wearing thin.

01:14.657 --> 01:17.660
How can you shoot what you can't see?

01:17.744 --> 01:18.745
Mr. Miller!

01:19.329 --> 01:20.914
-No, thank you.
-[feedback squeals]

01:20.997 --> 01:22.332
Hey, Cody.

01:23.666 --> 01:26.503
My name is Holden. I'd like to help you.

01:27.045 --> 01:29.672
-Tell me what's going on.
-I gotta talk to my wife.

01:29.756 --> 01:31.424
-[Holden] All right.
-She's the only one.

01:31.508 --> 01:32.759
I understand.

01:32.842 --> 01:35.553
For the moment,
is there anything else we can get you?

01:35.637 --> 01:37.639
Get these fucking people away.

01:37.722 --> 01:38.640
Okay.

01:41.226 --> 01:44.229
-Okay...
-[camera shutters clicking]

01:45.313 --> 01:46.815
[sighs]

01:46.898 --> 01:48.942
If I can get them to back off,

01:49.484 --> 01:52.779
will you... relax with Ms. Curtwell?

01:53.696 --> 01:56.324
Give us some time to reach your wife.

01:59.160 --> 02:00.328
[Miller] Okay.

02:00.411 --> 02:01.454
Thank you.

02:05.959 --> 02:08.503
Keep the snipers. Back out the perimeter.

02:08.586 --> 02:10.505
If he starts firing,
we'll have to storm the place.

02:10.588 --> 02:12.674
They're making me nervous.
Imagine what they're doing to him.

02:12.757 --> 02:15.218
He has no criminal history.
He's clearly having an episode.

02:15.301 --> 02:17.637
We need to keep him calm
and wear him down.

02:18.054 --> 02:19.556
Get rid of those reporters.

02:21.349 --> 02:22.767
[indistinct radio chatter]

02:22.851 --> 02:24.561
All right, guys. Back it up!

02:24.644 --> 02:27.689
-[man] All right. Let's go. Back it up.
-[man 2] Move back.

02:29.858 --> 02:30.859
How am I doing?

02:32.443 --> 02:33.945
[woman gasps]

02:37.198 --> 02:39.367
-[Miller] You see me?
-Oh, God.

02:41.119 --> 02:42.871
Yes, I can see you!

02:44.330 --> 02:47.292
-What do you see?
-[Holden] I can see that you're naked.

02:47.876 --> 02:49.460
I can see that you're cold.

02:49.544 --> 02:52.630
[thunder rumbling]

02:57.510 --> 02:59.345
[indistinct radio chatter]

02:59.429 --> 03:01.264
Is there a phone?
Can we get him on the line?

03:01.347 --> 03:04.309
-He's got it off the hook.
-That was his demand, talk to his wife?

03:04.392 --> 03:06.352
Took all day to find her.
She's on her way.

03:06.436 --> 03:08.688
-You're not bringing her.
-I want her to calm him.

03:08.771 --> 03:10.440
Her presence might have
the opposite effect.

03:14.193 --> 03:16.321
Hi, Mrs. Miller? Don't get out.

03:16.404 --> 03:19.866
I'm Holden Ford from the FBI.
Do you understand the situation?

03:19.949 --> 03:23.369
-Cody's got some people in there?
-What happened this morning?

03:23.453 --> 03:24.412
I don't know.

03:24.954 --> 03:27.999
I tried to get him sectioned on Sunday,
but I haven't seen him since.

03:28.082 --> 03:31.377
They told me he stole a shotgun,
robbed a liquor store?

03:31.461 --> 03:32.754
Was he delusional? Violent?

03:32.837 --> 03:34.756
He's not violent.

03:34.839 --> 03:37.884
He's been saying that he's invisible
for a while now.

03:37.967 --> 03:40.011
Truly invisible.
He's been seeing a doctor.

03:40.094 --> 03:41.262
Did the doctor diagnose him?

03:41.888 --> 03:43.556
Cody wouldn't tell me.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.100
He's taking medication,
but he might've stopped.

03:46.184 --> 03:48.478
-What kind of medication?
-I'm not sure.

03:49.479 --> 03:50.438
Here's his doctor.

03:50.521 --> 03:52.273
You tried to get him sectioned?

03:52.357 --> 03:55.526
He kept talking to people that weren't
there, saying they could see him.

03:56.402 --> 03:59.030
I told him I was gonna leave him
if he didn't go to the hospital.

03:59.113 --> 04:01.574
-You gave him an ultimatum?
-[Mrs. Miller sobbing] I'm sorry.

04:02.492 --> 04:04.827
-I feel awful.
-This is not your fault.

04:05.286 --> 04:06.704
Has he hurt anyone?

04:06.788 --> 04:09.374
Not that we know about.
I'm sending you along for now.

04:09.874 --> 04:11.292
[bangs on roof of car]

04:14.212 --> 04:15.755
Have someone call his doctor.

04:15.838 --> 04:17.799
Get his wife to tell him
she won't leave him.

04:17.882 --> 04:20.969
We need more information.
Let's see if we can get him on the line.

04:22.845 --> 04:24.097
Cody!

04:24.180 --> 04:26.182
Everything okay in there?

04:29.143 --> 04:31.104
I'd really like to know
what's going on in there.

04:31.187 --> 04:33.064
I promise you, we can work this out.

04:40.905 --> 04:42.031
Where's my wife?

04:42.532 --> 04:46.244
[Holden] It's a difficult situation.
Taking a while to get her here.

04:46.327 --> 04:48.538
-She doesn't want to talk to me?
-[Holden] That's not it.

04:48.621 --> 04:51.249
She is very worried about you.

04:51.791 --> 04:54.210
-You talked to her?
-[Holden] On the phone.

04:55.253 --> 04:58.214
-Maybe you could talk to her on the phone.
-No!

05:00.049 --> 05:01.634
She has to be here.

05:06.681 --> 05:10.226
-[Holden] I understand your frustration.
-[Miller] What do you understand?

05:10.310 --> 05:13.980
[Holden] Not being able to communicate
with a trusted loved one.

05:15.231 --> 05:16.774
What do you want to say to her?

05:17.775 --> 05:18.985
Why would I tell you?

05:22.238 --> 05:23.740
Maybe I can help.

05:25.658 --> 05:26.743
I don't think so.

05:30.538 --> 05:33.875
[screams]

05:33.958 --> 05:36.627
[all clamoring]

05:46.179 --> 05:48.806
[theme music playing]

07:26.112 --> 07:27.321
[door opens]

08:27.673 --> 08:28.508
[exhales]

09:28.317 --> 09:29.819
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

09:40.830 --> 09:45.751
You followed procedure. You did your job.
You did everything by the book.

09:45.835 --> 09:48.588
He took hostages.
He knew there'd be consequences.

09:48.671 --> 09:50.673
-He thought he was invisible.
-You're not his shrink.

09:50.756 --> 09:53.926
You're not responsible for diagnosing him.
That's not your remit.

09:54.885 --> 09:58.055
These things happen in real time,
and we are the last responders.

09:58.139 --> 10:01.684
If an operation's gonna go south,
this is not the worst outcome.

10:01.767 --> 10:03.436
Stay focused on what we do.

10:03.519 --> 10:06.397
If I did everything by the book,
it begs the question--

10:06.480 --> 10:10.484
This place is pretty much the benchmark
for excellence in law enforcement.

10:11.694 --> 10:14.572
In the rest of the world,
hostage negotiation's on its way out.

10:14.655 --> 10:17.617
You think the Israelis bothered
to negotiate at Entebbe last year?

10:19.869 --> 10:24.457
You didn't lose one hostage or bystander.
That's how we measure success.

10:26.459 --> 10:29.086
And your courses are a big hit
in the summer.

10:29.170 --> 10:31.255
I actually think
you should be teaching more.

10:31.339 --> 10:33.466
-You're putting me out to pasture.
-No.

10:33.549 --> 10:35.551
I'm putting you to work
where it really counts.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.011
Despite what happened.

10:37.094 --> 10:39.347
Because  of what happened, Holden.

10:39.847 --> 10:40.890
It seasoned you.

10:45.102 --> 10:46.103
Thank you, sir...

10:47.104 --> 10:48.105
but I'd rather not.

10:48.189 --> 10:49.774
Well, this is awkward.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.695
I'd like you to sleep on it
over the weekend...

10:56.322 --> 10:58.491
because you start full-time on Monday.

11:06.791 --> 11:11.003
This is how we find ourselves
completely out of control.

11:12.213 --> 11:15.716
The fugitive has already killed
a police officer that morning in Austin.

11:17.134 --> 11:19.553
He's taken two nine-millimeter rounds
in the ass,

11:19.637 --> 11:21.472
grabbed a ten-year-old boy as a hostage,

11:21.555 --> 11:23.391
and he's holed up
in a suburban neighborhood

11:23.474 --> 11:25.601
crawling with women and small children.

11:26.769 --> 11:28.687
Now we must focus on one thing:

11:29.355 --> 11:31.065
de-escalation.

11:31.649 --> 11:35.319
San Antonio's chief of police arrives
and starts using a bullhorn,

11:35.403 --> 11:38.739
which more than effectively
intimidates our hostage-taker.

11:40.199 --> 11:43.244
Coming at anyone with an attitude of
"I'm right, you're wrong"

11:43.327 --> 11:45.454
assumes that they're of rational mind.

11:47.623 --> 11:50.376
We must establish communication.

11:51.752 --> 11:54.880
Non-threatening communication.

11:55.756 --> 11:57.049
Ascertain demands,

11:57.133 --> 12:00.261
concede nothing, reject nothing,
just listen.

12:01.804 --> 12:03.389
Listen to what he has to say.

12:05.391 --> 12:08.227
Try understanding him
instead of trying to dominate him.

12:09.228 --> 12:10.729
Look for common ground.

12:10.813 --> 12:12.815
Find commonality.

12:13.357 --> 12:17.153
And if it feels like you're buying time,
well... that's because you are.

12:17.695 --> 12:20.739
But it's the key
to making any perp feel heard.

12:20.823 --> 12:23.284
-[chime sounds]
-[indistinct chatter]

12:23.367 --> 12:24.869
[Holden] Our goal is no body bags.

12:24.952 --> 12:27.329
That is the hostage negotiator win-win.

12:29.290 --> 12:31.876
And I'm in my office on Friday
for anyone who has questions

12:31.959 --> 12:34.253
about the psychological strategies exam.

12:43.095 --> 12:45.806
[man] Wanton, indiscriminate murder.

12:45.890 --> 12:48.517
Seemingly random, serendipitous.

12:48.601 --> 12:50.269
Each one, extremely violent.

12:50.352 --> 12:52.980
No explanation. No apparent reason.

12:53.063 --> 12:54.607
They weren't sexually assaulted,

12:54.690 --> 12:56.650
there was no attempt
to relieve them of valuables,

12:56.734 --> 12:58.360
they didn't know their assailant.

12:58.903 --> 13:02.198
Robert Violante and Stacy Moskowitz
were making out in their car

13:02.281 --> 13:05.493
when David Berkowitz walked up
and shot them both point-blank.

13:06.368 --> 13:08.704
Berkowitz killed six people
over two summers,

13:08.787 --> 13:10.748
wounding seven more. Why?

13:11.999 --> 13:14.376
Because a dog told him to do it.

13:15.753 --> 13:16.670
Now...

13:18.506 --> 13:22.259
we can say that the guy's crazy,
or that he's pretending that he's crazy.

13:22.676 --> 13:25.346
But if we're looking for a motive
we can understand,

13:25.429 --> 13:27.306
we suddenly find there is none.

13:27.890 --> 13:29.099
It's a void.

13:29.183 --> 13:30.518
It's a black hole.

13:36.232 --> 13:40.986
Forty years ago, your FBI was founded
hunting down John Dillinger,

13:41.445 --> 13:43.989
Baby Face Nelson, Machine Gun Kelly.

13:44.073 --> 13:46.742
Criminals who thumbed their noses
at society,

13:46.825 --> 13:49.078
but were basically in it
for personal gain.

13:50.037 --> 13:53.999
Now, we have extreme violence
between strangers.

13:54.959 --> 13:56.502
Where do we go...

13:57.670 --> 14:00.005
when motive becomes elusive?

14:09.515 --> 14:11.600
Excuse me, Professor Rathman?

14:13.852 --> 14:16.272
Holden Ford, Hostage Negotiation.

14:16.355 --> 14:17.565
Peter. Hi.

14:17.648 --> 14:21.277
I listened in on your class earlier.
What you were saying about crime today...

14:22.152 --> 14:23.863
I don't know, it really resonates.

14:23.946 --> 14:26.031
-Gets attention.
-Were you teaching this before Berkowitz?

14:26.115 --> 14:28.701
A version of it.
The headlines kind of fell into my lap.

14:28.784 --> 14:29.869
What got you started?

14:30.202 --> 14:32.621
Starkweather. Whitman.
Manson, of course.

14:32.705 --> 14:35.249
But Son of Sam kind of epitomizes now.

14:35.332 --> 14:39.420
It's as if... we don't know anymore
what moves people to kill one another.

14:39.503 --> 14:42.256
Used to be you find a victim
with 50 stab wounds,

14:42.339 --> 14:45.092
you look for the jilted lover,
the ex-business partner.

14:45.342 --> 14:49.138
Now... it could be a random run-in
with a disgruntled mailman.

14:49.221 --> 14:52.558
It's a different era.
No more "Just the facts, ma'am."

14:52.641 --> 14:54.810
That's television. And reruns.

14:55.394 --> 14:57.479
-Crime has changed.
-Right.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.733
Do you... want to grab a beer?

15:02.192 --> 15:03.193
Yeah, okay.

15:04.153 --> 15:06.071
[Rathman] Look at the unprecedented events

15:06.155 --> 15:08.866
that have occurred
in the past decade and a half.

15:08.949 --> 15:10.492
A president assassinated.

15:10.576 --> 15:13.245
Fighting an unpopular war
that we didn't win.

15:13.329 --> 15:15.748
National Guard killing
four college students.

15:15.831 --> 15:18.292
-You can hardly wrap your mind around it.
-Watergate.

15:18.375 --> 15:21.921
Our democracy is vanishing into what?

15:22.004 --> 15:23.672
Is that what all this is about?

15:23.923 --> 15:25.925
Just a response to turmoil?

15:26.008 --> 15:29.094
The government used to be, symbolically,
a parental institution.

15:29.178 --> 15:31.639
Now? It's a free-for-all.

15:31.722 --> 15:35.184
The world barely makes any sense,
so it follows that crime doesn't either.

15:35.267 --> 15:38.729
You and I could theorize all night,
but the truth is, I don't fucking know.

15:38.812 --> 15:41.023
-I don't know either.
-No one does.

15:41.106 --> 15:42.691
But we're supposed to, right?

15:42.775 --> 15:47.237
Sure, but here's the troubling thing:
no one's even asking the questions.

15:51.116 --> 15:52.034
We are.

15:52.701 --> 15:53.702
We are.

15:56.622 --> 15:57.915
Mm!

15:59.333 --> 16:02.586
Next time, let's discuss
Lee Harvey Oswald as Oedipus.

16:04.463 --> 16:05.589
-Thank you.
-Anytime.

16:17.893 --> 16:19.395
-Hey.
-Hey.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.063
What are you looking at?

16:21.814 --> 16:22.940
I like your outfit.

16:23.482 --> 16:25.901
What is that, a jumpsuit?
What do you call that?

16:25.985 --> 16:28.112
-This? I call it a jumpsuit.
-Stylish.

16:28.195 --> 16:30.698
What do you call that?
You look like a Mormon.

16:31.156 --> 16:32.282
You look like my dad.

16:32.366 --> 16:33.409
Is he a Mormon?

16:33.492 --> 16:34.910
No, but he looks like one.

16:34.994 --> 16:36.203
So does mine.

16:36.286 --> 16:38.622
He bought me this suit,
as a matter of fact.

16:38.706 --> 16:41.041
Did he buy you those nice shiny shoes?

16:41.458 --> 16:42.334
Yes.

16:42.918 --> 16:45.421
I have one brown pair and one black pair.

16:46.255 --> 16:48.590
I've got sneakers,
but I had to buy those myself.

16:48.674 --> 16:51.844
What kind of grown-up lets their parents
choose their clothes for them?

16:53.679 --> 16:56.682
-Are you coming on to me?
-How do you like my approach?

17:02.354 --> 17:03.981
You having a good time?

17:04.064 --> 17:05.733
-I will be.
-Huh!

17:05.816 --> 17:07.026
It's my birthday today.

17:07.109 --> 17:09.361
Happy birthday. How old are you?

17:09.445 --> 17:12.197
-Twenty-four.
-You don't look old enough to be in here.

17:12.281 --> 17:14.533
-What are you, a narc?
-FBI, actually.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.786
Special Agent Holden Ford.

17:17.870 --> 17:19.204
Wow.

17:20.998 --> 17:23.042
-Can you tell?
-Everybody can tell.

17:23.625 --> 17:24.501
You got a gun?

17:24.585 --> 17:26.795
I have one,
but I'm not gonna show it to you.

17:26.879 --> 17:27.796
Nuts.

17:28.630 --> 17:31.175
I'm a teacher.
Right up the road at Quantico.

17:31.258 --> 17:32.384
What do you teach?

17:33.260 --> 17:36.263
Hostage negotiation, such as it is.

17:36.346 --> 17:39.183
-Holy cow.
-You really think I look like a narc?

17:39.266 --> 17:41.435
-Are you kidding?
-I don't see it.

17:41.518 --> 17:43.228
You stick out like a sore thumb.

17:44.646 --> 17:48.400
Well, I'm not here to...
infiltrate the Black Panthers.

17:48.734 --> 17:52.404
Those guys are hardly Black Panthers.
They're engineering students.

17:52.863 --> 17:54.323
You should go talk to them.

17:54.406 --> 17:57.367
I'm sure the FBI's in need
of some great-looking black dudes.

17:57.451 --> 18:00.621
-You've got the wrong idea about me.
-You gonna book me?

18:00.704 --> 18:01.872
Maybe.

18:01.955 --> 18:02.998
Handcuffs?

18:08.170 --> 18:10.506
I'm here to see this really cool band
from Detroit.

18:11.048 --> 18:12.424
You ever been to Detroit?

18:13.217 --> 18:14.760
Yes, actually. I was a--

18:18.430 --> 18:20.891
I was a brick agent there
for a couple of years.

18:21.308 --> 18:24.645
I can't believe they're here.
They used to play PJ's in Corktown.

18:25.395 --> 18:26.814
-You know Corktown?
-Sure.

18:26.897 --> 18:29.358
-It looked like a furniture store.
-They always sold liquor.

18:29.441 --> 18:32.820
The whole furniture thing was just a front
that started during Prohibition.

18:32.903 --> 18:34.321
Where are you really from?

18:34.863 --> 18:36.532
[sighs] Everywhere.

18:36.615 --> 18:38.283
But the Midwest, right?

18:38.367 --> 18:41.328
I grew up in the Midwest,
but I was born in Brooklyn.

18:41.411 --> 18:43.789
You do not seem like a guy from New York.

18:44.873 --> 18:47.042
You don't seem like a girl from Corktown.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.380
Buy you a drink?

18:54.800 --> 18:57.511
-[rock music playing]
-[vocalizing]

20:56.463 --> 20:59.007
[music continues]

21:36.837 --> 21:39.047
-[Holden] What's your name?
-Debbie.

21:42.384 --> 21:44.803
-You want some pot?
-Is that a trick question?

21:44.886 --> 21:45.887
Come on.

21:46.263 --> 21:48.390
Are you serious?
No, that's completely inappropriate.

21:48.473 --> 21:50.225
Come on, it's my birthday.

21:50.309 --> 21:52.811
Oh, Jesus, you're not gonna
drink and drive, are you?

21:52.894 --> 21:54.354
You've been plying me with booze.

21:54.438 --> 21:56.732
Don't you think
that's kind of a mixed message?

22:01.069 --> 22:01.987
You coming?

22:06.033 --> 22:07.909
[engine starts]

22:12.080 --> 22:15.334
[indistinct chatter]

22:15.417 --> 22:17.544
[rock music plays softly]

22:20.005 --> 22:23.383
So what does a brick agent
get up to in Detroit?

22:23.884 --> 22:25.761
Mostly corralling Army deserters.

22:26.595 --> 22:29.097
Guys AWOL from Vietnam
trying to get to Canada.

22:30.390 --> 22:31.600
Too scared to go back.

22:32.267 --> 22:34.603
Young guys. Same age I was.

22:35.103 --> 22:36.688
So you were a snitch?

22:38.940 --> 22:40.942
There's worse things than being a snitch.

22:44.029 --> 22:46.615
Maybe this'll loosen you up.

22:47.949 --> 22:49.743
[Holden exhales]

22:50.243 --> 22:51.870
God, you are making me nervous.

22:52.704 --> 22:54.289
You are such a goody-goody.

22:55.874 --> 22:57.709
What are you, some kind of honey trap?

22:58.210 --> 23:00.253
I've been warned to watch out
for women like you.

23:02.005 --> 23:03.215
You mean normal ones?

23:08.595 --> 23:10.305
[sighs]

23:10.889 --> 23:13.475
